By the time Atu became a young man, the First Tarasa War
broke out. The island where Atu lived was divided into two
factions and was in the midst of chaos.

Tarasa and Fotizona were special places where residents from
both factions lived, and ownership of this island became one
of the points of contention in the war. Skirmishes between
the residents were a daily occurrence and gradually became
more intense.

In the midst of such chaos, two factions emerged. Atu, a
resident of Tarasa who supported Fotizona, and Agonia, a
resident of Fotizona who supported Tarasa.

They repeated the war game every day, sometimes using words,
but most of the time resorting to violence. At the center of
it all were always Atu and Agonia.

The common point between these two completely different
types was that they had no interest in the conflict over the
island. They used the war as an excuse to release their
excess energy.

Atu and Agonia were originally best friends, and the reason
they became enemies was simply because it seemed more fun to
be enemies. They also joined opposing factions for the same
reason, despite their different backgrounds.

The two of them decided to leave the island when they got
tired of playing war games. The place they headed to was the
Fotizona Empire, the largest power in the region. It was a
suitable place to escape from the cramped island and go
towards.
